Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity, suggesting possible diabetic nephropathy or another renal pathology. Hemoglobin A1c is low, which may reflect recent hypoglycemia or anemia. No evidence of urinary tract infection is present. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment of glycemic status.
